item.title: My very first model (dark Sword)
item.dc:creator: @wayzey wayzey
item.description:
@wayzey wrote:

No offence and I really don’t want you to take any offense to this comment but that file is gzipped so the only real way for us to view it is in an RS server or by unpacking it and viewing it as a .dat in datmaker or rsvm. Really you need to take screenshots because what you’ve done here is well pointless, it’s a hard process we must endure to view and judge your model and since it’s one of your first probably noone will go to the effort of viewing and judging it as really it takes too much work.

To take screenshots in any windows OS use the PrtScn button and then open paint and press the keys ctrl+v to paste a screenshot of your screen in paint. Then just crop it, upload to photobucket or another image sharing site and put the link inside [img][/img]
